<section class="sec reveal" id="qbwp-framework">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The decision framework</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Five factors that decide the right plan.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Every QuickBooks plan question reduces to these five. Map your business honestly against each, and the right product and tier becomes obvious &mdash; or obviously needs a ProAdvisor&rsquo;s read.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for f in factors %}
      <div class="dc-card">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ f.num }}</span>
        <h3>{{ f.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ f.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbwp-patterns" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Common business patterns</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">What we typically recommend, by business profile.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">These aren&rsquo;t rules &mdash; every business has nuances &mdash; but they&rsquo;re the patterns we see most often. Find the one closest to your situation, then book the call to confirm the specifics.</p>
